def trans_box(i):
    plt.figure(figsize=(20,8),facecolor='white')
    plt.subplots_adjust(hspace=0.4)
    plt.subplot(2,3,1)
    sns.boxplot(data=df_num[i],orient='h')
    plt.title('Original',fontdict={'fontsize':15})
    plt.xlabel(i,fontdict={'fontsize':15})
    plt.subplot(2,3,2)
    sns.boxplot(data=np.sqrt(df_num[i]),orient='h')
    plt.title('Sqroot',fontdict={'fontsize':15})
    plt.xlabel(i,fontdict={'fontsize':15})
    plt.subplot(2,3,3)
    sns.boxplot(data=(df_num[i])**2,orient='h')
    plt.title('Square',fontdict={'fontsize':15})
    plt.xlabel(i,fontdict={'fontsize':15})
    plt.subplot(2,3,4)
    sns.boxplot(data=np.log(df_num[i]),orient='h')
    plt.title('Log',fontdict={'fontsize':15})
    plt.xlabel(i,fontdict={'fontsize':15})
    plt.subplot(2,3,5)
    sns.boxplot(data=np.cbrt(df_num[i]),orient='h')
    plt.title('Cuberoot',fontdict={'fontsize':15})
    plt.xlabel(i,fontdict={'fontsize':15})
    plt.show()
In [234]:
for i in df_num.columns:
    trans_box(i)

Outlier Treatment¶

In [242]:
Q1 = df.quantile(0.25)
Q3 = df.quantile(0.75)
IQR = Q3 - Q1
df_outlier = df[((df < (Q1 - 1.5 * IQR)) |(df > (Q3 + 1.5 * IQR))).any(axis=1)]
print(df_outlier.shape)

(2407, 14)
In [243]:
## percentage of Outliers
df_outlier.shape[0]*100/len(df)
Out[243]:
32.717140138643465

As the percentage of Outliers is 32.71%, removing is not possible¶

Instead of removing Outliers we can replace it with median¶

In [244]:
def df_out(col):
    Q3,Q1 = np.nanpercentile(col,[75,25])
    IQR = Q3-Q1
    UL = Q3+1.5*IQR
    LL = Q1-1.5*IQR
    return UL,LL
In [245]:
# First replacing the Outliers in to 'Null' values
for column in df_num.columns:
    UL, LL = df_out(df[column])
    df[column]= np.where((df[column] > UL)|(df[column] < LL),np.nan, df[column])
